pageContext.description: Apparently a rough casting; mouth of socket is uneven; mould marks very prominent and sharp, and have not been reduced by filing. Edge blunt and unground. Piece of waste metal left inside loop.
pageContext.patina: On one side, very dark patina (almost black), with traces of golden bronze colour, and of green near edge. On the other green and brown mottled.
pageContext.surface: Smooth and in very good condition.
pageContext.collection: June 1936,Mr. A. G. Ravening,60 Holland Park Mews, W.II,(Who is trying to sell it to Truro Museum)
pageContext.site: England,Cornwall,Doddington Point,Found (June 1936) on beach at Doddington Point
